{
  "_doc": "TradingView → OMS Webhook Templates for DayX Trial 695",
  "_updated": "2026-03-20",
  "_notes": [
    "Trial 695 uses partial exits (46.7% at T1), so we need TWO alert templates.",
    "Template A: For strategies WITHOUT partial exits (simple entry/exit).",
    "Template B: For Trial 695 WITH partial exits (uses strategy.order.action).",
    "",
    "HOW TO SET UP IN TRADINGVIEW:",
    "1. Add the PineScript strategy to a QQQ 1-minute chart",
    "2. Right-click strategy name → 'Add Alert on ...'",
    "3. Condition: 'DayX Trial 695' → 'Order fills only'",
    "4. Paste Template B into the 'Message' field (minified JSON on one line)",
    "5. Set Webhook URL to: https://oms-481888403086.us-east1.run.app/webhook",
    "6. Enable the alert",
    "",
    "IMPORTANT:",
    "- The token must match OMS_WEBHOOK_SECRET env var on Cloud Run",
    "- {{strategy.order.action}} returns 'buy' or 'sell' for EVERY order fill",
    "- For partial T1 exit: action='sell', qty=46.7% of position (correct)",
    "- For full T2/stop exit: action='sell', qty=remaining shares (correct)",
    "- For short entry (sell_rip): action='sell', for short exit: action='buy'",
    "- OMS _normalize_action maps buy→open(buy), sell→open(sell)",
    "- The 'comment' field helps track exit reasons in OMS logs"
  ],

  "_template_A_simple (no partial exits)": {
